  <answer><![CDATA[<div class="c-page-content">
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/594483304a5f4b47844b444df2c9d975" href="/{localLink:umb://document/594483304a5f4b47844b444df2c9d975}" title="Mayrhofen">Mayrhofen</a> offers several beginner-friendly walks. The Stilluptal features an easy valley floor path with waterfalls and a turquoise reservoir, accessible by a private bus. The Penken Panoramaweg is an 8.1km trail perfect for families, offering panoramic views and activities like mountain scooters and zorb balls, plus a route extending to the Brandberg dairy farm for cheese tasting. For those with buggies, the Ahorn Leisure Trail includes bird-watching stations and viewing platforms, making it an accessible and enjoyable option.</p>
